The patient is a 48-year-old male with a prosthetic valve who presented with endocarditis caused by Corynebacterium propinquum. The narrative states the organism was resistant to daptomycin, and the patient was successfully treated with ceftriaxone. The adverse event is 'Endocarditis'. This is an infectious disease process caused by the identified bacteria and is not an adverse drug reaction to daptomycin. Since daptomycin was not the cause of the condition but rather the agent against which the bacteria showed resistance, the causality is determined to be Doubtful. The event is serious as it involved a prosthetic heart valve endocarditis, requiring medical intervention.

