```

The patient developed acute profound thrombocytopenia (platelets 2 K/uL) shortly after receiving eptifibatide. The temporal association is consistent with drug-induced thrombocytopenia. Discontinuation of the drug (dechallenge) resulted in the recovery of platelet levels, which strongly suggests causality. Thrombocytopenia is a known, well-documented adverse reaction of eptifibatide (listed in RSI section 5.2). The reaction led to the postponement of a planned urgent surgery, which constitutes an 'other serious medical event' or 'hospitalization' impact, rendering it serious. Naranjo score calculation: +2 (event after drug admin), +2 (improvement after dechallenge), +2 (no alternative cause mentioned as primary), +1 (known reaction profile) = 7.

